1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
3 SUBCOMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
FOR
5
6
7 SUBCOMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
8 An Act relating to agricultural education; requiring
the State Department of Agriculture to operate the Ag
9 in the Classroom program; stating program purpose;
prescribing Department duties under the program;
10 clarifying authority for the program; directing
receipt of funds; authorizing the Department to apply
11 for and use certain funds for program purposes;
amending 47 O.S. 2021, Section 1104.3, which relates
12 to the Ag in the Classroom Education Revolving Fund;
increasing the fee allocated to the fund from
13 Agricultural Awareness license plates; allowing
appropriation and receipt of other monies to the
14 fund; clarifying expenditure authority; requiring
certain monies to be expended for program expansion;
15 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
16
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5-60.7 of Title 2, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23
24
Req. No. 12715 Page 1
1 A. The State Department of Agriculture shall operate an "Ag in
2 the Classroom Program" for the purpose of educating students about
3 agriculture within Oklahoma.
4 B. The Department shall:
5 1. Develop curriculum for pre-kindergarten through twelfth
6 grade Ag in the Classroom programs for urban and rural schools;
7 2. Provide training and workshops for Oklahoma teachers who
8 utilize Ag in the Classroom curriculum;
9 3. Utilize existing Department resources and related programs
10 to develop and enhance the Ag in the Classroom Program; and
11 4. Cooperate with the State Department of Education and the
12 Oklahoma State University Cooperative Extension Service as needed in
13 development and operation of the Ag in the Classroom Program.
14 C. The State Department of Agriculture shall have exclusive
15 control and authority over the Ag in the Classroom Program and no
16 other state agency, board, commission, department, or other entity
17 of state government shall have authority with respect to the
18 Program. The Department shall directly receive all funds obtained
19 for the Ag in the Classroom Program pursuant to Section 1104.3 of
20 Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The Department may apply for,
21 accept, and use any gift, grant, or bequest from any source for the
22 purpose of discharging its duties under this section.
23 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 1104.3, is
24 amended to read as follows:
Req. No. 12715 Page 2
1 Section 1104.3. A. Twenty-four Dollars ($24.00) Twenty-seven
2 Dollars ($27.00) of the fee authorized by Section 1135.5 of this
3 title for Agricultural Awareness license plates shall be deposited
4 to the Ag in the Classroom Education Revolving Fund created in
5 subsection B of this section.
6 B. 1. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a
7 revolving fund for the State Department of Agriculture to be
8 designated the "Ag in the Classroom Education Revolving Fund". The
9 fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year
10 limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
11 Department pursuant to the provisions of subsection A of this
12 section, appropriated or apportioned by the Legislature and received
13 as federal grants or funds, municipal contributions, private
14 contributors, and received from other sources, for duties associated
15 with this act. All monies accruing to the credit of such fund are
16 hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
17 Department for the purpose of Ag in the Classroom Education Program.
18 Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the
19 State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with the
20 Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
21 approval and payment. The State Department of Agriculture shall
22 have exclusive control over the Ag in the Classroom Program and no
23 other state agency, board, commission, department, or other entity
24
Req. No. 12715 Page 3
1 of s tate government shall have authority with respect to any
2 expenditure from the revolving fund.
3 2. All monies received by the Department above Twenty-four
4 Dollars ($24.00) of the fee for the Agricultural Awareness license
5 plates shall be allocated toward the expansion of the Ag in the
6 Classroom Education Program into urban areas.
7 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
